1
00:00:01,702 --> 00:00:04,271
Narrator: In the fifth round
of voting for the election

2
00:00:04,304 --> 00:00:08,241
of the 13th chairman,
pariston placed first.

3
00:00:08,275 --> 00:00:10,244
However, since he
failed to secure

4
00:00:10,277 --> 00:00:12,246
a majority of the valid votes,

5
00:00:12,279 --> 00:00:15,649
those in the top eight
must now hold a runoff.

6
00:00:17,284 --> 00:00:19,453
Cutie: I lost.
Why, you might ask?

7
00:00:19,486 --> 00:00:21,989
Well, the truth is
I haven’t lost.

8
00:00:22,022 --> 00:00:25,325
Our beloved pariston
will help me realize my vision,

9
00:00:25,359 --> 00:00:28,929
and a cute hunter association
will soon be enacted!

10
00:00:28,962 --> 00:00:31,565
Bisky: Well,
that nutty old geezer--

11
00:00:31,598 --> 00:00:33,667
I mean netero--

12
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:37,137
i’m sure everyone knows
just how crazy he could be,

13
00:00:37,171 --> 00:00:39,340
but I still feel
this is worth mentioning.

14
00:00:39,373 --> 00:00:41,175
The fiasco with the ants proves

15
00:00:41,208 --> 00:00:44,244
that you can’t solve a crisis
with lofty morals,

16
00:00:44,278 --> 00:00:45,679
and that’s a fact!

17
00:00:50,284 --> 00:00:53,320
Saccho: I swear i’ll still
work for the association

18
00:00:53,353 --> 00:00:54,688
behind the scenes.

19
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:56,456
I won’t name names,

20
00:00:56,490 --> 00:00:59,426
but I do hope you vote for
someone who’s worth supporting.

21
00:01:01,028 --> 00:01:04,598
Sanbica: Um, to all those
who voted for me,

22
00:01:04,631 --> 00:01:06,533
i’d like to say thank you.

23
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:08,169
B-but, please, no more.

24
00:01:08,202 --> 00:01:09,336
I can’t take this!

25
00:01:10,504 --> 00:01:13,507
( Linne murmuring )

26
00:01:13,540 --> 00:01:15,308
( Grunts )

27
00:01:15,342 --> 00:01:17,411
Eh?

28
00:01:17,444 --> 00:01:18,712
( Sighs )

29
00:01:18,745 --> 00:01:20,146
♪

30
00:01:20,180 --> 00:01:46,406
( Singing in Japanese )

31
00:01:48,475 --> 00:01:52,679
♪ You can smile again

32
00:01:52,713 --> 00:01:54,748
( singing in Japanese )

33
00:01:54,781 --> 00:01:58,618
♪ You can fly away

34
00:01:58,652 --> 00:02:03,824
( singing in Japanese )

35
00:02:04,091 --> 00:02:06,026
♪

36
00:02:21,275 --> 00:02:23,277
Hisoka: Yes? Hello?

37
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:25,279
Can you believe it?

38
00:02:25,312 --> 00:02:27,447
I got a map.

39
00:02:27,481 --> 00:02:29,550
It outlines the exact routes

40
00:02:29,583 --> 00:02:32,786
and the destinations
for all six airships.

41
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:34,487
Of all the vessels,

42
00:02:34,521 --> 00:02:38,358
they would seem to be
on one of the remaining two.

43
00:02:38,392 --> 00:02:40,494
Do you want me
to send a picture?

44
00:02:40,527 --> 00:02:44,331
I’ll use texture surprise
to doctor it a little, though.

45
00:02:45,866 --> 00:02:47,301
Illumi: No, thank you.

46
00:02:47,334 --> 00:02:49,803
There was an idiot here
carrying a map,

47
00:02:49,837 --> 00:02:52,807
and I already know
which airship killua took.

48
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:55,343
Hisoka: I see.

49
00:02:55,375 --> 00:02:57,744
Oh, right. He has a spy.

50
00:03:01,248 --> 00:03:02,416
( Grass rustles )

51
00:03:04,151 --> 00:03:06,420
Tsubone: Am I being watched?

52
00:03:06,453 --> 00:03:08,221
I’m not so senile

53
00:03:08,255 --> 00:03:11,759
i’d let someone tail me
while i’m tailing another, am I?

54
00:03:15,662 --> 00:03:18,698
I’ve sensed eyes on me
for some time,

55
00:03:18,732 --> 00:03:20,767
ever since the mission began.

56
00:03:22,169 --> 00:03:23,737
They’re quite far away,

57
00:03:23,770 --> 00:03:26,439
yet I still
can’t shake them off.

58
00:03:26,473 --> 00:03:29,710
This is the first time
that’s happened.

59
00:03:29,743 --> 00:03:32,379
They must be very good indeed.

60
00:03:34,448 --> 00:03:36,350
Come back here quickly, amane!

61
00:03:36,383 --> 00:03:37,351
Time to fly!

62
00:03:37,384 --> 00:03:38,352
Amane: Right!

63
00:03:38,385 --> 00:03:40,187
( Wind blowing )

64
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:41,621
Tsubone: Fortunately for us,

65
00:03:41,655 --> 00:03:44,825
it appears that the clouds
have come out tonight.

66
00:03:44,858 --> 00:03:49,496
Master killua is sure
to use that to his advantage.

67
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:55,502
And there he goes.

68
00:03:56,603 --> 00:03:58,805
You’re late! Let’s go!

69
00:03:58,839 --> 00:03:59,773
Amane: Right!

70
00:04:01,808 --> 00:04:04,744
Narrator: Tsubone’s ability,
which is known as rider’s high,

71
00:04:04,778 --> 00:04:06,546
allows her to transform herself

72
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:09,817
into various
types of vehicles at will.

73
00:04:09,850 --> 00:04:13,153
However, the vehicles
are fueled by the rider’s aura,

74
00:04:13,187 --> 00:04:16,323
which means that she
cannot use her ability alone.

75
00:04:18,292 --> 00:04:20,561
Tsubone: No one
can watch us from the ground

76
00:04:20,594 --> 00:04:23,664
when we’re above the clouds,
no matter how strong the scope.

77
00:04:23,697 --> 00:04:25,933
Amane, we’ll take down

78
00:04:25,966 --> 00:04:28,936
any suspicious aircraft
we see in the area.

79
00:04:28,969 --> 00:04:30,270
Amane: Yes!

80
00:04:30,304 --> 00:04:31,806
( Illumi sighs )

81
00:04:31,839 --> 00:04:33,674
Well...

82
00:04:33,707 --> 00:04:37,644
We still have some time
before either airship arrives.

83
00:04:37,678 --> 00:04:41,482
I suppose I should
go lend hisoka a hand.

84
00:04:41,515 --> 00:04:43,484
Hunter: Nothing
out of the ordinary here.

85
00:04:43,517 --> 00:04:47,221
We haven’t seen
any sign of the target.

86
00:04:48,922 --> 00:04:51,892
Loupe: We’ve lost all contact
with point c!

87
00:04:51,925 --> 00:04:54,895
Teradein: Point a
is reporting all clear.

88
00:04:54,928 --> 00:04:56,496
Should we send them over?

89
00:04:56,530 --> 00:04:58,899
Bushidora: They might
also be compromised.

90
00:04:58,932 --> 00:05:01,968
It’s possible
that illumi’s manipulating them,

91
00:05:02,002 --> 00:05:05,472
so he may already have
full control of the area.

92
00:05:05,506 --> 00:05:08,609
Loupe: Are you saying he’s
already killed over 20 people?

93
00:05:08,642 --> 00:05:10,277
Bushidora: Look,
it doesn’t matter

94
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:12,345
how many amateurs
we throw at him.

95
00:05:12,379 --> 00:05:13,881
I think we should warn the pros

96
00:05:13,914 --> 00:05:16,917
who are going after
the needle people immediately.

97
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:18,852
( Phone line ringing )

98
00:05:18,886 --> 00:05:21,622
Teradein: Latoon and kenzaki
aren’t answering.

99
00:05:21,655 --> 00:05:22,990
Bushidora: What?

100
00:05:23,023 --> 00:05:24,992
Teradein: The two airships
that they were following

101
00:05:25,025 --> 00:05:26,460
are in close proximity.

102
00:05:27,661 --> 00:05:29,796
We can assume...

103
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:31,832
Bushidora: It seems
I should get going.

104
00:05:31,865 --> 00:05:33,800
This is my chance to prove

105
00:05:33,834 --> 00:05:37,438
that i’m worthy
to lead the pure paladin squad.

106
00:05:37,471 --> 00:05:39,406
Loupe: What about the election?

107
00:05:39,439 --> 00:05:42,275
Bushidora: Those who are able
should still go vote.

108
00:05:42,309 --> 00:05:44,378
Even if we exclude
everyone who’s hunting,

109
00:05:44,411 --> 00:05:46,747
we can still finish
in the top four.

110
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:50,284
Teradein: Yes. We must
continue voting in the election.

111
00:05:50,317 --> 00:05:52,719
We may not be able
to predict the outcome,

112
00:05:52,753 --> 00:05:55,656
but i’d still rather not sway
the vote through abstentions.

113
00:05:55,689 --> 00:05:59,526
Loupe: I don’t understand
why we don’t hire temp hunters.

114
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:01,929
If we can show people
that we’re trying to carry on

115
00:06:01,962 --> 00:06:03,730
the spirit
of the hunter association,

116
00:06:03,764 --> 00:06:05,399
we just might be able to win

117
00:06:05,432 --> 00:06:07,467
some of the votes
that are defaulting to pariston.

118
00:06:07,501 --> 00:06:09,036
Bushidora: He’s right.

119
00:06:09,069 --> 00:06:11,271
We should post a notice at once!

120
00:06:11,305 --> 00:06:12,273
( Teradein grunts )

121
00:06:14,308 --> 00:06:15,709
♪

122
00:06:15,742 --> 00:06:18,411
Loupe: If everything works out
the way I think it will,

123
00:06:18,445 --> 00:06:20,380
the temp hunters will be killed.

124
00:06:20,414 --> 00:06:21,849
What better way to guarantee

125
00:06:21,882 --> 00:06:23,984
they miss
the next round of voting?

126
00:06:24,017 --> 00:06:27,487
But if I told him that,
i’m sure teradein would object.

127
00:06:27,521 --> 00:06:30,057
We should actually be abstaining

128
00:06:30,090 --> 00:06:34,361
so we can ensure that this round
of votes is thrown out.

129
00:06:34,394 --> 00:06:38,899
Teradein is too honest,
and bushidora is too careless.

130
00:06:38,932 --> 00:06:40,333
Pariston: You’re telling me

131
00:06:40,367 --> 00:06:42,803
Mr. Teradein
has requested temp hunters?

132
00:06:42,836 --> 00:06:45,772
Magnificent!
Yes, a wonderful request!

133
00:06:45,806 --> 00:06:48,742
Do everything in your power
to make it happen!

134
00:06:48,775 --> 00:06:51,311
Oh, you don’t need
to be concerned about me.

135
00:06:51,345 --> 00:06:52,947
In fact,
if there’s no upper limit

136
00:06:52,980 --> 00:06:55,483
on the number
of temp hunters we can send,

137
00:06:55,516 --> 00:06:58,419
spread the word,
and take everyone you want.

138
00:06:58,452 --> 00:07:00,721
If you come across
anything you want to ask

139
00:07:00,754 --> 00:07:02,556
or tell me while on the job,

140
00:07:02,589 --> 00:07:04,758
just feel free
to contact me anytime,

141
00:07:04,791 --> 00:07:06,826
and if anything
needs to be improved,

142
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:09,563
i’m positive we’ll
be able to work it out.

143
00:07:13,901 --> 00:07:15,069
( Sighs )

144
00:07:15,102 --> 00:07:17,838
( Snickers )

145
00:07:19,706 --> 00:07:22,409
What an excellent trio.

146
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:24,577
I do like them.

147
00:07:25,779 --> 00:07:27,881
They’re so easy.

148
00:07:30,784 --> 00:07:34,955
Teradein: The vote’s invalid
because turnout was 91.2%

149
00:07:34,988 --> 00:07:37,390
what is happening?!

150
00:07:38,492 --> 00:07:40,060
Loupe: Teradein!

151
00:07:40,093 --> 00:07:43,096
Everyone who was pursuing
the needle people was wiped out,

152
00:07:43,130 --> 00:07:45,766
our members, the camera crew,
the temp hunters,

153
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:47,467
and bushidora!

154
00:07:47,501 --> 00:07:48,969
( Teradein gasps )

155
00:07:49,002 --> 00:07:50,470
It can’t be!

156
00:07:50,504 --> 00:07:52,139
It was illumi!

157
00:07:52,172 --> 00:07:56,677
He must have hired dozens
of incredibly powerful soldiers!

158
00:07:56,710 --> 00:07:58,378
♪

159
00:07:58,412 --> 00:08:00,814
Hisoka: More like one magician.

160
00:08:07,521 --> 00:08:09,423
Tsubone: I haven’t
felt those eyes on me

161
00:08:09,456 --> 00:08:10,891
ever since we took flight,

162
00:08:10,924 --> 00:08:14,561
and that means that we
really were being tailed before.

163
00:08:18,165 --> 00:08:19,700
Killua: The clouds have cleared.

164
00:08:19,733 --> 00:08:22,135
Well, it should be fine

165
00:08:22,169 --> 00:08:24,405
this far from the hospital.

166
00:08:24,438 --> 00:08:27,708
If anyone sees alluka
when we go inside,

167
00:08:27,741 --> 00:08:30,444
tsubone will say that
her power has been revealed,

168
00:08:30,477 --> 00:08:33,413
and she’ll use that excuse
to take us home immediately,

169
00:08:33,447 --> 00:08:36,417
and this’ll all be over.

170
00:08:36,450 --> 00:08:39,820
But if I clear the area
so nobody sees us,

171
00:08:39,853 --> 00:08:42,756
that’ll only make it easier
for illumi to act.

172
00:08:44,157 --> 00:08:46,626
And taking this airship
directly to the hospital

173
00:08:46,660 --> 00:08:49,029
would be pretty tough.

174
00:08:49,062 --> 00:08:52,098
Gotoh suggested driving a car
through the front door,

175
00:08:52,132 --> 00:08:54,101
and that might be our best bet.

176
00:08:54,134 --> 00:08:55,469
Eh?

177
00:08:55,502 --> 00:08:57,571
( Dials telephone )

178
00:08:59,473 --> 00:09:03,043
Canary, i’m having
some trouble reaching gotoh.

179
00:09:03,076 --> 00:09:04,811
Canary: So am I.

180
00:09:04,845 --> 00:09:07,548
Killua: Then I need you to tell
hishita and all of the others

181
00:09:07,581 --> 00:09:10,050
to send cars to
the following three locations.

182
00:09:10,083 --> 00:09:12,152
As soon as possible, okay?

183
00:09:12,186 --> 00:09:14,188
Canary: Yes, I understand.

184
00:09:17,691 --> 00:09:19,560
Killua: I’m sure
we lost the ground pursuit

185
00:09:19,593 --> 00:09:21,462
by flying above the clouds.

186
00:09:21,495 --> 00:09:23,764
We’ll be fine
until we’re in the car.

187
00:09:23,797 --> 00:09:27,100
After that, we have to pick
the best route to the hospital.

188
00:09:30,938 --> 00:09:33,507
Gon, hang in there.

189
00:09:42,883 --> 00:09:45,586
Killua: Okay.
Nice timing, hishita.

190
00:09:46,687 --> 00:09:48,656
Looping around took more time,

191
00:09:48,689 --> 00:09:51,625
but now we’re 60 kilometers
from the hospital.

192
00:09:51,658 --> 00:09:53,093
They’ll never find us.

193
00:09:57,130 --> 00:09:58,565
To the hospital!

194
00:09:58,599 --> 00:10:00,568
Hishita: Yes, understood, sir.

195
00:10:00,601 --> 00:10:01,569
( Car door closes )

196
00:10:01,602 --> 00:10:03,537
( Tires squealing )

197
00:10:08,008 --> 00:10:09,543
Killua: What’s wrong?

198
00:10:09,576 --> 00:10:11,578
Hishita:
People in front of the car.

199
00:10:11,612 --> 00:10:12,880
♪

200
00:10:12,913 --> 00:10:14,581
Killua: Oh, no.

201
00:10:14,615 --> 00:10:15,983
Needle people.

202
00:10:16,016 --> 00:10:19,186
Impossible. How?

203
00:10:19,219 --> 00:10:20,787
No way they followed us!

204
00:10:20,821 --> 00:10:22,956
Was it the car?

205
00:10:22,990 --> 00:10:24,592
Did they follow the car?

206
00:10:24,625 --> 00:10:27,661
Hishita, gun it! Run ’em down!

207
00:10:27,694 --> 00:10:29,596
They’re all beyond help, anyway!

208
00:10:29,630 --> 00:10:32,066
Hishita: I’m afraid
I can’t do that...

209
00:10:33,634 --> 00:10:36,904
Not without a direct order
from master illumi.

210
00:10:36,937 --> 00:10:38,605
( Killua gasps )

211
00:10:38,639 --> 00:10:39,907
What?!

212
00:10:39,940 --> 00:10:42,443
♪

213
00:10:48,549 --> 00:10:51,185
We’re completely surrounded.

214
00:10:51,218 --> 00:10:52,152
( Gasps )

215
00:10:56,823 --> 00:10:57,957
Impossible.

216
00:10:59,126 --> 00:11:00,761
How is he here?

217
00:11:02,629 --> 00:11:04,965
Illumi, how?

218
00:11:06,934 --> 00:11:08,769
This can’t be happening,

219
00:11:08,802 --> 00:11:10,771
unless he knew
which airship we were on.

220
00:11:12,072 --> 00:11:14,041
No, even if he knew,

221
00:11:14,074 --> 00:11:15,642
it doesn’t make sense.

222
00:11:15,676 --> 00:11:17,244
We flew way above the clouds.

223
00:11:17,277 --> 00:11:19,846
He couldn’t have followed us
on the ground.

224
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:22,149
Illumi: Hello, kil.

225
00:11:22,182 --> 00:11:24,685
You’re hiding something
about alluka.

226
00:11:24,718 --> 00:11:26,987
Now tell me what it is.

227
00:11:28,722 --> 00:11:30,857
Killua: Do I use godspeed
to drag hishita

228
00:11:30,891 --> 00:11:33,260
out of the car
and use it to escape?

229
00:11:33,293 --> 00:11:36,863
Or go back to the airship
and try to escape by air?

230
00:11:36,897 --> 00:11:40,134
If I were alone,
either one of those would work.

231
00:11:40,167 --> 00:11:42,736
But not now that i’ve
gotta keep alluka safe.

232
00:11:43,804 --> 00:11:45,873
How did you know we were here?

233
00:11:45,906 --> 00:11:48,008
Illumi: If I tell you,

234
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:50,877
then will you agree
to hand alluka over?

235
00:11:50,911 --> 00:11:52,579
Killua: Not gonna happen.

236
00:11:52,613 --> 00:11:53,814
Forget I asked.

237
00:11:55,282 --> 00:11:56,316
Physically alluka’s

238
00:11:56,350 --> 00:11:58,285
only as strong as a normal kid.

239
00:11:58,318 --> 00:12:01,254
A single attack
from one of the needle people

240
00:12:01,288 --> 00:12:02,623
could be lethal.

241
00:12:03,790 --> 00:12:05,191
What do I do?

242
00:12:07,794 --> 00:12:09,663
My only choice...

243
00:12:09,696 --> 00:12:11,831
Is to summon nanika.

244
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:14,301
( Killua gasps )

245
00:12:14,334 --> 00:12:17,037
Tsubone: It was me.

246
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:20,106
I was the fool
who fell prey to this deception.

247
00:12:20,140 --> 00:12:21,341
Alluka: Hey!

248
00:12:21,375 --> 00:12:23,110
Look! It’s tsubone!

249
00:12:23,143 --> 00:12:25,145
Tsubone: The missis can see

250
00:12:25,179 --> 00:12:27,615
everything I see
through this eyepiece.

251
00:12:27,648 --> 00:12:31,619
I’m afraid this is all my fault.

252
00:12:31,652 --> 00:12:34,788
I bet that she transmitted
the video to you,

253
00:12:34,821 --> 00:12:36,756
didn’t she, master illumi?

254
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:38,025
Illumi: Bingo.

255
00:12:38,058 --> 00:12:40,127
Tsubone was my spy.

256
00:12:41,628 --> 00:12:43,730
Tsubone: When the clouds
had cleared away,

257
00:12:43,764 --> 00:12:45,966
I felt those eyes
watching me again,

258
00:12:45,999 --> 00:12:47,901
and I suddenly realized
the truth,

259
00:12:47,935 --> 00:12:51,038
that the timing was too perfect
to be a coincidence.

260
00:12:51,071 --> 00:12:55,275
Illumi: Ah, so you actually
felt us watching, did you?

261
00:12:56,376 --> 00:12:58,645
You’re really something.

262
00:12:58,679 --> 00:13:03,050
But, although you sensed us,
you still couldn’t disobey mom,

263
00:13:03,083 --> 00:13:05,786
so you left
the eyepiece in place.

264
00:13:05,819 --> 00:13:08,855
Tsubone: Yes.
I’ll admit that’s it exactly.

265
00:13:08,889 --> 00:13:10,858
Alluka: Tsubone,

266
00:13:10,891 --> 00:13:13,861
give me the nail
from your middle finger.

267
00:13:13,894 --> 00:13:15,262
( Illumi gasps )

268
00:13:15,295 --> 00:13:17,664
♪

269
00:13:17,698 --> 00:13:20,267
Tsubone: Yes, absolutely.

270
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:22,068
( Nail crunches )

271
00:13:22,102 --> 00:13:24,605
For you, my young master.

272
00:13:27,875 --> 00:13:29,076
Alluka: And, tsubone,

273
00:13:29,109 --> 00:13:31,678
give me the nail
from your ring finger now.

274
00:13:31,712 --> 00:13:33,214
Tsubone: Of course!

275
00:13:33,247 --> 00:13:36,117
That’s a very easy request,
my dear.

276
00:13:36,149 --> 00:13:37,617
( Nail crunches )

277
00:13:38,852 --> 00:13:40,020
Killua: Thanks, tsubone.

278
00:13:40,053 --> 00:13:41,288
I appreciate it.

279
00:13:41,321 --> 00:13:43,223
( Nen whooshes )

280
00:13:48,328 --> 00:13:50,163
Tsubone: There, master killua.

281
00:13:50,197 --> 00:13:53,000
You should be able
to make your wish now.

282
00:13:53,033 --> 00:13:57,204
Amane and I will pay
whatever price you incur.

283
00:13:57,237 --> 00:14:00,073
I ruined your well-laid plans.

284
00:14:00,107 --> 00:14:01,609
I’m so sorry.

285
00:14:01,642 --> 00:14:04,145
Please allow us to make amends.

286
00:14:05,946 --> 00:14:07,915
Illumi: So will you do it?

287
00:14:07,948 --> 00:14:09,149
Fine with me.

288
00:14:09,183 --> 00:14:11,452
If you want to wish
for gon’s healing,

289
00:14:11,485 --> 00:14:14,288
this is the protocol that you’ll
have to follow, right?

290
00:14:15,789 --> 00:14:18,759
If you can sacrifice those two
to kill me,

291
00:14:18,792 --> 00:14:20,827
i’m sure
you won’t have any problem

292
00:14:20,861 --> 00:14:24,164
sacrificing a bunch of strangers
to save your friend gon.

293
00:14:25,299 --> 00:14:27,201
Rule number five.

294
00:14:27,234 --> 00:14:31,105
The same person can’t
make a wish twice in a row.

295
00:14:33,073 --> 00:14:35,776
Hisoka: Now, then,
would it be more fun

296
00:14:35,809 --> 00:14:38,812
to kill alluka,
sparking killua’s wrath,

297
00:14:38,846 --> 00:14:41,315
or would it be better
to spare alluka,

298
00:14:41,348 --> 00:14:44,885
save gon,
and make an enemy of illumi?

299
00:14:46,486 --> 00:14:48,955
Choices, choices.

300
00:14:50,290 --> 00:14:52,225
Illumi: Bear in mind
that, if you say yes,

301
00:14:52,259 --> 00:14:53,961
i’ll be happy to die.

302
00:14:53,994 --> 00:14:56,396
Your intra-mission
will have succeeded.

303
00:14:58,131 --> 00:15:00,867
Killing family
is against the rules,

304
00:15:00,901 --> 00:15:03,303
but the thing
that will Grant your wish...

305
00:15:05,138 --> 00:15:07,374
Isn’t part of our family.

306
00:15:07,407 --> 00:15:09,342
( Killua gasping )

307
00:15:12,813 --> 00:15:14,248
Illumi: Even if it turns out

308
00:15:14,281 --> 00:15:16,817
that rule number five
doesn’t apply to killua,

309
00:15:16,850 --> 00:15:19,820
i’ll gladly die
to save the rest of the family,

310
00:15:19,853 --> 00:15:22,823
and i’ll do so
without hesitation.

311
00:15:22,856 --> 00:15:26,893
Killua will suffer
for the rest of his life.

312
00:15:26,927 --> 00:15:30,864
I, on the other hand, will
live on forever in his heart.

313
00:15:31,932 --> 00:15:33,100
( Killua gasping )

314
00:15:33,133 --> 00:15:35,102
Illumi: Well, go on.

315
00:15:35,135 --> 00:15:38,839
I’m offering you a deal, killua.

316
00:15:38,872 --> 00:15:40,907
Take my life,
and, in exchange,

317
00:15:40,941 --> 00:15:43,310
you will get to make
your wish for gon.

318
00:15:43,343 --> 00:15:45,779
Sound fair?

319
00:15:45,812 --> 00:15:46,913
( Killua gasping )

320
00:15:46,947 --> 00:15:49,383
Hisoka: If I spare alluka,

321
00:15:49,416 --> 00:15:53,086
illumi will die, and killua
won’t become enraged,

322
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:56,757
so, if gon is healed, I neither
gain nor lose anything.

323
00:15:58,158 --> 00:16:01,395
In that case,
my course is clear.

324
00:16:01,428 --> 00:16:04,865
I should kill alluka
to incur killua’s wrath,

325
00:16:04,898 --> 00:16:08,268
then kill killua
to incur illumi’s wrath.

326
00:16:08,302 --> 00:16:10,838
Isn’t that
the best of both worlds?

327
00:16:10,871 --> 00:16:13,173
♪

328
00:16:19,246 --> 00:16:20,180
Killua: Nanika...

329
00:16:22,449 --> 00:16:25,886
I wish for tsubone’s hand
to be healed now.

330
00:16:27,387 --> 00:16:29,155
( Illumi gasps )

331
00:16:29,189 --> 00:16:31,091
Nanika: ’kay.

332
00:16:32,192 --> 00:16:34,161
( Illumi grumbles )

333
00:16:34,194 --> 00:16:36,930
Nanika: Hand. Hand.

334
00:16:36,964 --> 00:16:40,201
Killua: Tsubone,
put out your left hand.

335
00:16:40,234 --> 00:16:42,870
Tsubone: Master killua,
what are you--

336
00:16:42,903 --> 00:16:44,104
killua: Just do it.

337
00:16:51,144 --> 00:16:56,383
Nanika is better at destroying
than she is at healing.

338
00:16:56,416 --> 00:16:58,852
If she wants to heal,

339
00:16:58,886 --> 00:17:01,188
she has to be
touching the target,

340
00:17:01,221 --> 00:17:03,590
but...

341
00:17:03,624 --> 00:17:05,993
( Tsubone gasps )

342
00:17:06,026 --> 00:17:07,060
Nanika: ’kay.

343
00:17:07,094 --> 00:17:08,495
( Giggles ) Killua!

344
00:17:08,529 --> 00:17:10,998
Give me a hug!
Did I do good?

345
00:17:11,031 --> 00:17:13,433
Killua: Of course.
You did great.

346
00:17:13,467 --> 00:17:15,502
That was amazing, nanika.

347
00:17:15,536 --> 00:17:17,638
( Nanika giggles )

348
00:17:17,671 --> 00:17:19,306
( Sighs )

349
00:17:19,339 --> 00:17:20,640
( Murmurs )

350
00:17:20,674 --> 00:17:23,010
♪

351
00:17:23,043 --> 00:17:26,547
Killua: Nanika’s the one
who calls me killua.

352
00:17:26,580 --> 00:17:30,417
Healing tires her out,
so she sleeps,

353
00:17:30,450 --> 00:17:33,053
but that’s all there is.

354
00:17:34,521 --> 00:17:37,290
After someone’s made a wish
to heal something,

355
00:17:37,324 --> 00:17:40,227
nanika’s never demanded
anything cruel in return,

356
00:17:40,260 --> 00:17:42,028
not once!

357
00:17:42,062 --> 00:17:43,130
( Sighs )

358
00:17:43,163 --> 00:17:46,566
Nanika is kinder than anyone.

359
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:49,570
The cursed ones
are the ones making the wishes.

360
00:17:52,005 --> 00:17:54,074
Treat nanika
like an object again...

361
00:17:55,609 --> 00:17:58,011
And you’re no longer
my big brother.

362
00:18:03,584 --> 00:18:06,153
Illumi: I understand. Ten-four.

363
00:18:06,186 --> 00:18:10,290
If you can heal gon without
assuming any risk at all,

364
00:18:10,324 --> 00:18:13,527
I think that’s wonderful.

365
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:16,196
But i’m afraid that still
doesn’t change the fact

366
00:18:16,230 --> 00:18:18,065
that nanika is dangerous

367
00:18:18,098 --> 00:18:20,934
and my questions
remain unanswered.

368
00:18:22,503 --> 00:18:26,374
Even now, there’s something
you’re hiding from me,

369
00:18:26,406 --> 00:18:28,541
like how milluki’s
rule number five

370
00:18:28,575 --> 00:18:30,477
doesn’t apply to you,
for instance.

371
00:18:31,745 --> 00:18:34,248
So until you tell me
everything you know,

372
00:18:34,281 --> 00:18:36,650
alluka will never be free.

373
00:18:38,318 --> 00:18:39,986
Killua: Idiot!

374
00:18:40,020 --> 00:18:42,723
That’s exactly why
I can’t tell you anything.

375
00:18:42,756 --> 00:18:45,392
If you knew
the last rule, you’ll--

376
00:18:45,425 --> 00:18:47,694
no, not just you.

377
00:18:47,728 --> 00:18:50,998
All of you, you’d put
needles in my head again,

378
00:18:51,031 --> 00:18:53,534
and you’d do it
with smiles on your faces.

379
00:18:56,403 --> 00:18:59,339
Amane: Master killua,
i’ll take you to the hospital.

380
00:19:01,441 --> 00:19:04,411
Teradein: Captain bushidora
of the pure paladin squad

381
00:19:04,444 --> 00:19:07,614
lost his life in pursuit
of the wicked hunter

382
00:19:07,648 --> 00:19:11,318
that we had hoped
to bring to justice.

383
00:19:11,351 --> 00:19:13,253
This is proof positive

384
00:19:13,287 --> 00:19:16,490
that a coldblooded evil
is lurking among us.

385
00:19:16,523 --> 00:19:19,326
That’s why I regret telling you

386
00:19:19,359 --> 00:19:22,596
that the pure paladin squad
does not have the power

387
00:19:22,629 --> 00:19:25,665
to bring the hunter
or hunters to justice.

388
00:19:25,699 --> 00:19:27,100
It’s out of our hands.

389
00:19:27,134 --> 00:19:30,104
Everyone,
this is an urgent matter

390
00:19:30,137 --> 00:19:33,374
that the association
must unite to resolve at once!

391
00:19:33,407 --> 00:19:35,075
That is why our goal

392
00:19:35,108 --> 00:19:38,378
is to ensure
that voter turnout exceeds 95%

393
00:19:38,412 --> 00:19:40,547
and that the winner
has a clear majority.

394
00:19:40,581 --> 00:19:43,384
There must be no question
about the result!

395
00:19:43,417 --> 00:19:47,121
That is why we are currently
in negotiations with morel,

396
00:19:47,154 --> 00:19:49,757
who has strong ties with
the former chairman’s faction

397
00:19:49,790 --> 00:19:52,393
in hopes that he
will be our new captain.

398
00:19:52,426 --> 00:19:55,262
At the same time,
we are prepared to reveal

399
00:19:55,295 --> 00:19:57,798
the name, face,
and ability of the killers.

400
00:19:57,831 --> 00:20:01,668
We’ll do whatever it takes
to prevent any further tragedy.

401
00:20:01,702 --> 00:20:04,271
If you’re with us,
then I implore you all

402
00:20:04,304 --> 00:20:06,306
to vote and show your support.

403
00:20:07,641 --> 00:20:11,612
So save the hunters
by voting for teradein.

404
00:20:11,645 --> 00:20:13,247
♪

405
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:16,116
Morel: Yeah, the thing is,

406
00:20:16,149 --> 00:20:18,518
I think I remember
turning you down.

407
00:20:18,552 --> 00:20:21,622
Teradein:
But can’t you reconsider?

408
00:20:21,655 --> 00:20:23,757
Morel: I was pretty close
to the chairman,

409
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:26,326
and I helped wipe out the ants,

410
00:20:26,360 --> 00:20:29,530
but i’m not the warrior
you think I am.

411
00:20:29,563 --> 00:20:33,567
The operation required support,
and I was chosen to supply it.

412
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:36,503
That doesn’t necessarily mean
i’m strong, you know.

413
00:20:36,537 --> 00:20:37,538
Teradein: Yes. However--

414
00:20:37,571 --> 00:20:40,240
morel: Look, you saw the top 16.

415
00:20:40,274 --> 00:20:43,210
I am a sea hunter!
You know what I can’t handle?

416
00:20:43,243 --> 00:20:45,579
Dry land,
and I won’t be tied to it.

417
00:20:45,612 --> 00:20:47,147
Teradein: Give it time!

418
00:20:47,181 --> 00:20:48,616
Morel: Look...

419
00:20:48,649 --> 00:20:51,218
I get that you’re in a hurry
to end this election,

420
00:20:51,251 --> 00:20:53,153
so why don’t you
just tell your supporters

421
00:20:53,187 --> 00:20:55,256
to vote for pariston?

422
00:20:55,289 --> 00:20:58,392
I mean, personally i’d
rather die than vote for him.

423
00:20:59,693 --> 00:21:02,062
Oh, just one more thing,
and i’m done.

424
00:21:02,095 --> 00:21:04,531
If you even think
of releasing their identity,

425
00:21:04,565 --> 00:21:06,634
you and a bunch
of other daredevil idiots

426
00:21:06,667 --> 00:21:08,369
are gonna die. You hear me?

427
00:21:08,402 --> 00:21:10,271
And you’re too weak
to call yourselves

428
00:21:10,304 --> 00:21:12,273
the pure paladin squad,
so quit it!

429
00:21:12,306 --> 00:21:14,508
I won’t work with anyone
who won’t listen to me

430
00:21:14,541 --> 00:21:17,744
when I give them fair warning,
and I don’t want to be chairman!

431
00:21:17,778 --> 00:21:19,747
- I’m done here!
- ( Hangs up )

432
00:21:23,450 --> 00:21:26,153
Narrator: The seventh round
of voting is complete,

433
00:21:26,186 --> 00:21:29,289
and it results in a revote
between the top four.

434
00:21:29,323 --> 00:21:30,758
♪

435
00:21:30,791 --> 00:22:04,758
( Singing in Japanese )

436
00:22:04,758 --> 00:22:06,758
